## 🎯 Why These Updates Matter

**From Your Observations**:
- **Pricing**: $19/mo felt limiting for 50 vols / 15 ministries. Your church example validates Growth tier ($49/mo).
- **Workflow Flexibility**: Different churches want different approval workflows. MVP now supports all 4 modes.
- **Calendar Feeds**: Volunteers want iCal sync to Google Calendar / Outlook. Now MVP feature.
- **Reminders**: Email or SMS, not both. Users should choose. Now configurable per volunteer.
- **Self-Contained**: Some churches prefer not to push back to Planning Center. Now primary option.

**Why It Strengthens VolunteerCalendar**:
- Broader appeal (supports multiple workflows, not just centralized)
- Higher perceived value (calendar feeds, flexible reminders, no ChMS lock-in)
- Better product-market fit (your church is the template, not an edge case)
- Clearer differentiation (Planning Center has rigid workflow; VC is flexible)
- Faster validation (interviews now test core value props)

